narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Discussion of the role of opposition in a democracy. A lot of the course is about the relationship between process and outcomes to the democratic model--to what extent does how you made a decision matter to its legitimacy? We also discussed free speech, civil disobedience, and developing democracies.Take it if you're interested in the subject.
I would certainly recommend the course to somebody interested in the subject--or to someone with a passing interest in political science.
A solid underclassman seminar. Perhaps a little old hat for those who have taken advanced EP&E classes before, but generally enjoyable, with only two major assignments and 5 short reading responses.
